Bulelwa Ndudula, the wife of slain Eastern Cape department of social development chief of staff Sakhekile Ndudulawas dealt a heavy blow this morning after she was condemned to prison for another month. The ruling was made earlier today as the 44-year-old woman who is accused of killing her husband by shooting him seven times on the morning of September 14 appeared in the East London Magistrate s Court.The court heard that police had not yet completed their investigation and therefore were granted an extension until December 14.The date has been set down for Ndudula&#8217;s next court appearance.